<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Ex-J.C. Penney President Dies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	DALLAS (AP) -- A memorial service was scheduled Monday for Jack  
B. Jackson, a former president of J.C. Penney Co., who died 
Thursday at the age of 83. 
</P>
<P>
	Jackson, a native of Sherman, Texas, began working at the  
retailer while in college and rose through the ranks to become 
president. 
</P>
<P>
	In a news release, J.C. Penney said Jackson was named president  
in 1972 and retired in 1976 after 38 years with the company. 
</P>
<P>
	Jackson was a trustee of Austin College in Sherman and bred show  
horses at his ranch in Aubrey, Texas. 
</P>
<P>
	He is survived by a brother, a sister, two sons and a daughter,  
five grandchildren and two great-grandchildren. 



  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
