<CATEGORY> entertainment </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Van Damme Wants To Remake Image </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- After five marriages and confessions about  
cocaine use, Jean-Claude Van Damme wants to remake his image. 
</P>
<P>
	``I have to reinvent the brand name, because I'm a brand name,''  
Van Damme says in Sunday's Daily News. ``Arnold (Schwarzenegger) 
knew how to do that.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Van Damme is back in theaters with ``Universal Soldier: The  
Return,'' a sequel. He says he feels ``indestructible'' after 
remarrying Gladys Portugues, making her wife No. 3 and No. 5, and 
that the drug problem he went public about last year is ``Gone. Oh 
yeah, gone.'' 
</P>
<P>
	``I'll be successful no matter what because you cannot stop a  
guy who believes in himself,'' he said. ``If I don't make it in a 
movie, I can be the new guy on TV. I can do, like, a romantic James 
Bond, French-accented comedy, like `To Catch a Thief.' And people 
will say, `Hey, cool guy!''' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
