<HEADLINE> Amtrak Train Smashes Car, Kills 3 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	VANCE, Ala. (AP) -- An Amtrak train smashed into a car on Sunday,  
killing three people in the car. 
</P>
<P>
	Tuscaloosa County Sheriff Ted Sexton said the passenger train  
carrying 161 passengers plowed into the car, pushing it about 50 
yards. Sexton says the train was traveling about 75 mph. 
</P>
<P>
	The car failed to stop at the crossing, investigators said. The  
names of the victims were not immediately released. 
</P>
<P>
	The train was traveling from New Orleans to New York City.  
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
