<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Strawberry Hits Homer in Triple-A </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	BUFFALO, N.Y. (AP) -- Darryl Strawberry hit a home run Sunday,  
connecting for the first time in his comeback bid as the Triple-A 
Columbus Clippers beat Buffalo 14-9 in 10 innings. 
</P>
<P>
	Batting fourth as the designated hitter, Strawberry went  
1-for-5, including a towering home run in the 10th for the New York 
Yankees' International League affiliate. 
</P>
<P>
	``I've hit a lot of home runs in my career,'' Strawberry said.  
``But baseball is a difficult game. It's just not going to come 
that easy. You just have to be patient with yourself, patient with 
the game.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Strawberry was suspended in April after his arrest on  
solicitation and drug charges. 
</P>
<P>
	Where and when -- not to mention if -- he'll play again for the  
Yankees isn't clear. His surgically repaired left knee must be 
healthy enough for him to play the outfield, and he has been 
struggling at the plate. 
</P>
<P>
	``I'm on track,'' said Strawberry, batting .256 with five RBIs  
for Columbus. ``I swing the bat well sometimes and sometimes I 
don't. That's just the way baseball is. Baseball's a funny game; I 
just take what it gives me.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Strawberry, who has 332 homers in his major league career, has  
claimed that this will be his final comeback. He hit 24 homers last 
year before being diagnosed with colon cancer. 
</P>
<P>
	``He's coming along fine,'' Columbus manager Trey Hillman said.  
``He's moving better than expected. He felt a little normal 
stiffness but nothing specifically related to the knee, so that's 
very encouraging.'' 
</P>
<P>
	If success can be measured by clicks of the turnstiles,  
Strawberry still has it. Friday's series opener drew 17,360 fans to 
Dunn Tire Park, the biggest crowd since the slumping Bisons' season 
opener. 
</P>
<P>
	Saturday night's crowd was still slightly larger than the season  
average despite competition from the telecast of the Buffalo Bills' 
first NFL preseason game and a popular county fair. Sunday's crowd 
was a healthy 13,842. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
