<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Plant Worker Dies of Blast Injuries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SMYRNA, Ga. (AP) -- One of seven workers injured in an explosion  
at a Georgia Power coal-burning plant died of burns early Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The victim, who wasn't identified, died between 4 a.m. and 5  
a.m., said Frankie Smith, a nursing supervisor at Grady Memorial 
Hospital. She said two other patients were in critical condition 
and two in satisfactory condition. 
</P>
<P>
	One worker was treated at the scene and released and another was  
treated at Grady and released. 
</P>
<P>
	The explosion happened about 1 p.m. Saturday at Plant McDonough,  
northwest of Atlanta, when a chemical that workers were using to 
clean equipment ignited with coal dust, fire officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	``Apparently what they were cleaning with flashed and it ignited  
some coal dust and exploded,'' Cobb County Fire Department 
spokesman Stephen Mize said. 
</P>
<P>
	The extent of damage to the plant was not immediately clear.  


  	   	
</P>
