<HEADLINE> Los Angeles Synagogue Vandalized </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LOS ANGELES (AP) -- Congregants of a Hollywood area temple  
arrived for weekend services to see a swastika and ``Jews die'' 
spray-painted on a wall, just days after a shooting spree at a 
Jewish community center in another part of the city. 
</P>
<P>
	``I believe it's a copycat thing,'' police Sgt. Sanford  
Rosenberg said of the graffiti discovered Saturday at Temple 
Knesset Israel. No arrests were made. 
</P>
<P>
	In the temple's mailbox, police found a letter that appeared to  
be anti-British. Temple president, Harvey Shield, is British. 
</P>
<P>
	Shield said that after a white supremacist's alleged shooting  
rampage Tuesday in the San Fernando Valley, temple members 
suggested he should increase security. 
</P>
<P>
	``My initial response was, let's not overreact so quickly,''  
Shield said. ``Now there is no question about it.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Shield said he planned to hire a security guard for the holy  
days in September. Police said patrols in the area would be stepped 
up. 
</P>
<P>
	White supremacist Buford Furrow was charged with killing a  
postal worker in suburban Chatsworth after he shot and wounded five 
others, four of them children, at the North Valley Jewish Community 
Center in Granada Hills. 
</P>
<P>
	Furrow allegedly told authorities the shooting spree was ``a  
wake-up call to America to kill Jews.'' 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
