<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Lockdown at San Quentin After Melee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN QUENTIN, Calif. (AP) --As many as 80 inmates were involved in  
a 1 1/2-hour melee at San Quentin Prison that injured five guards, 
officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	More than 460 prisoners remained under lockdown following the  
brawl Friday night in a cell block that houses some of San 
Quentin's most dangerous inmates. 
</P>
<P>
	One guard was treated at Marin General Hospital for minor  
injuries. Four others who were punched did not require hospital 
treatment, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
	Prison spokesman Vernell Crittendon said he didn't know how many  
inmates were injured, but none required medical attention. 
</P>
<P>
	The melee broke out as a number of inmates were returning from  
the dining hall about 7:25 p.m. Friday. An inmate apparently tried 
to block the door to the cell block, and a sergeant who tried to 
open it was attacked. 
</P>
<P>
	When 21 guards could not quell the melee, a rare second alert  
was called for extra personnel to subdue the inmates. Crittendon 
said that in his 22 years at the prison, a secondary response has 
been used only about a half-dozen times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
