<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Replay System Fails at Arrowhead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	KANSAS CITY, Mo. (AP) -- The first time the new instant replay  
system was used this season at Arrowhead Stadium, it failed. 
</P>
<P>
	The Tennessee Titans asked for a review of a pass play in the  
second quarter of Sunday night's exhibition game against the Kansas 
City Chiefs. The play had been was ruled incomplete. 
</P>
<P>
	Officials huddled around the replay booth on the Chiefs'  
sideline, but the video system didn't work. Referee Ron Blum walked 
across the field to Titans coach Jeff Fisher and told him the 
officials' findings were inconclusive. 
</P>
<P>
	It was later announced that the glitch was caused by a software  
problem and the Chiefs went to a backup system. 
</P>
<P>
	The replay was available in the press box and it appeared to  
show that a pass from quarterback Steve McNair to Kevin Dyson was 
incomplete. Dyson appeared to be juggling the ball as he was 
tackled. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
