<CATEGORY> washington </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> House-Hunting Clintons Visit N.Y. </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	RYE BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- President Clinton and Hillary Rodham  
Clinton toured a home listed at almost $2.3 million in this New 
York City suburb near the Connecticut line during a quick 
house-hunting trip Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The Clintons, accompanied by daughter Chelsea and the first  
lady's mother, Dorothy Rodham, were expected to visit several 
Westchester County homes. Reporters were kept at a distance from 
the first two houses and the White House did not provide 
information about them. 
</P>
<P>
	The first was secluded from the street, with a low stone wall  
and a tree-shaded drive. The sale price for the 4.14-acre property 
was $2.295 million, according to a sales listing available to real 
estate agents. It is described as having French windows, high 
ceilings, landscaping, a heated pool and a picturesque bridge and 
brook. 
</P>
<P>
	The second home was in South Salem, a bit to the north but also  
near the Connecticut border. 
</P>
<P>
	The Clintons interrupted their planned weekend stay at Camp  
David, the presidential retreat in Maryland. Mrs. Clinton, 
considering a run for the U.S. Senate, must move to New York by 
Election Day 2000 to be eligible. 
</P>
<P>
	They flew on a small Air Force jet rather than the Boeing 747  
that usually serves as Air Force One. 
</P>
<P>
	Last week, Mrs. Clinton looked at a seven-bedroom colonial house  
in Edgemont priced at $1.7 million. The White House did not say if 
that house was on their list Sunday. 
</P>
<P>
	The house, sheltered from the street by trees and rocky walls,  
is within walking distance of fashionable Scarsdale in southern 
Westchester County. The neighborhood is 22 miles north of Times 
Square and a half-hour by rail from Grand Central Terminal. 
</P>
<P>
	The house would be less of a financial burden on the Clinton's  
than the $3.8 million estate the first lady viewed in June. The 
Clintons earned $504,109 last year. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
