<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Boehringer Facing Shoulder Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	SAN DIEGO (AP) -- San Diego Padres pitcher Brian Boehringer will  
likely have surgery Tuesday for a partial tear in his right rotator 
cuff. 
</P>
<P>
	An MRI examination Saturday revealed the tear. The right-hander  
left Friday night's game against Florida after four innings. 
</P>
<P>
	San Diego has not yet placed Boehringer on the 15-day disabled  
list, but is expected to do so Monday. 
</P>
<P>
	Boehringer has been solid since becoming a starter early in the  
season. He is 6-5 with a 3.24 ERA. 
</P>
<P>
	Stan Spencer, demoted to Triple-A Las Vegas May 19, is expected  
to replace Boehringer. 
  	   	
</P>
</TEXT>
